frameDefinitions: An Entity is rated as unexpected for its context in terms of its magnitude.
These words relate to the relative ordering of two events or times.
This frame concerns an Evaluee being judged for its quality, i.e. how much it would probably be liked.
A Speaker states or makes known a future Eventuality on the basis of some Evidence.
Compared to its Competitors, a Standard is at the high end of a scale with respect to some Variable.
A Whole, an entity with a substructure, is assessed for whether or not it has all the necessary parts that are defined for it or for an entity of its kind.
frameExamples: The <t>entire</t> apple was riddled with worms .
<t>After</t> she arrived , she laid out her papers on the desk.
The Weather Centre <t>predicted</t> that it would be warmer but wet for the weekend.
The taxpayer is supporting a system <t>unmatched</t> in wastefulness .
What happens after the PPB investigation is <t>complete</t>?
listRoleDefinitions: The item which is described in terms of its expectedness in the context.

The <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is the event which is  being located in time with respect to some other event: The <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is profiled, in contrast to the <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen>, which is backgrounded.
The <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen> is the event  with respect to which the <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> is located.
The <fen>Focal_participant</fen> is the participant in the <fen>Focal_occasion</fen> which is profiled as being in a relation of relative time to the <fen>Landmark_occasion</fen>.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is being judged for its quality.
This role marks expressions that denote a scalar property of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> with respect to which the <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged.

This role marks expressions that indicate an event or state that is predicted to occur or hold at a future time. A single <fen>Eventuality</fen> may be expressed discontinuously in a raising construction. This role is also used for expressions that denote entities with variable attributes about which the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes predictions.
The <fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Speaker</fen> to transmit the prediction.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the prediction pertains. It is normally expressed as a PP Complement headed by <m>about</m>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the prediction is made.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes the prediction.
The <fen>Standard</fen> is the entity that is located closest to the end of the scale evoked by some <fen>Variable</fen>.
The <fen>Variable</fen> is a property that evokes a scale along which the <fen>Standard</fen> is located closest to one extreme in  comparison to its <fen>Competitors</fen>.
The role <fen>Competitors</fen> denotes the entities that are exceeded by the <fen>Standard</fen> with regard to the <fen>Variable</fen>.
The entity that is being assessed for having all its necessary parts or not.
The interval of time when the completeness of the entity is assessed.
listRoleExamples: The entire <fex>day</fex> was spent on the project .
<fex>Hours of eating and drinking</fex> followed the wedding ceremony.
Hours of eating and drinking followed <fex>the wedding ceremony</fex>.
The Beaujolais Nouveau is dazzling <fex>in freshness</fex>.
<fex>The institute</fex> forecast an increase in leisure spending of 15 per cent.
The events that would occur over the next several years had been predicted <fex>in the Bible</fex>.
John predicted <fex>last year</fex> that he would be finished by October.
Greenman predicted <fex>at a small dinner party</fex> that the market would rise again.
<fex>Hilary</fex> was unmatched by any politician in the country.
Hilary was unmatched <fex>by any politician in the country</fex>.
<fex>Our list of participants</fex> is still incomplete.
My journey to the dark side is <fex>now</fex> complete.
